data.title: Washburn Family
data.text:
We carry a large selection of Washburn guitars, in many models and colors. Washburn has a long history of making quality guitars in every price range, from models under $200, to models ranging from $200 to $450 and above. The quality and sound of their guitars has been a strong point for us as we have carried these guitars for a number of years. Washburn offers among the most features and quality for the money with workmanship, quality woods, tuners, and EQ systems (on acoustic electric models). Come on in and try one of these great guitars out in our acoustic room!

The big difference in buying a guitar from us is that we shop adjust and inspect every guitar to play well (Normally an $85.00 fee on customer repairs) which you would not normally get through a private seller, internet seller, or big box store.Enjoy the experience of a smaller, more comfortable shop versus a "Big Box" store. Where we hand adjust in our shop every guitar at no extra fee so you can enjoy a great playing guitar! Pictured are a number of different models we currently have in stock. Please call for availability as our stock changes with sales and new arrivals.

We carry a large selection of Oscar Schmidt guitars, in many models and colors. Oscar Schmidt is a sister line to Washburn guitars. Under the same ownership, they share a tradition of great guitars with American designs and excellent quality. These guitars are known for good play-ability, sound, and nice cosmetics at a more affordable price range than comparable Washburn models. Come on in and try one of these great guitars out in our acoustic room!

The big difference in buying a guitar from us is that we shop adjust and inspect every guitar to play well (Normally an $85.00 fee on customer repairs) which you would not normally get through a private seller, internet seller, or big box store. Enjoy the experience of a smaller, more comfortable shop versus a "Big Box" store. Where we hand adjust in our shop every guitar at no extra fee so you can enjoy a great playing guitar!

We offer a number of different Oscar Schmidt models including, but not limited to, their 3/4 size instruments, which are great for young beginners! These guitars also make great "travel" instruments for those adults, or young adults, on the go! Other "travel" sized guitars often go for double that of which you could get a 3/4 size Oscar Schmidt guitar for, making it an incredible value instrument, without sacrificing features or quality.

We also offer Oscar Schmidt's 12 string guitar models. Combined with our professional set up, valued at $85.00, these guitars make for an excellent affordable instrument for those looking for 12 strings in the $250.00 (approx) price range!
